  "prompt": "Should I use a mass gainer or whey protein to gain weight?",
  "response": "The choice between a mass gainer and whey protein depends on your specific goals and nutritional needs:\n\nMass Gainer:\n- Higher in calories\n- Contains carbohydrates and fats\n- Good for people struggling to eat enough calories\n- Easier to gain weight quickly\n- Less pure protein per serving\n- More expensive\n\nWhey Protein:\n- Higher protein concentration\n- Lower in calories\n- Helps muscle recovery and growth\n- More versatile\n- Less expensive\n- Better for lean muscle gain\n- Requires you to add additional calories through food\n\nRecommendation:\n- If you struggle to eat enough calories and want to gain weight quickly, use a mass gainer\n- If you want to build lean muscle and control your calorie intake, use whey protein\n- Consider consulting a nutritionist or fitness professional for personalized advice\n\nUltimately, proper diet, consistent training, and overall calorie surplus are key to gaining weight.",
